This paper is primarily focused on object recognition using convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of biologically inspired models, which could fall under the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of contextual information to improve object recognition, which could fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the relationship between human vision and machine vision, which could fall under the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
